Bootstrap is a framework development environment to create cross device websites.
It will make these websites interchangeably to look good, for varying sizes of displays, from small cell phones to
large screen monitors.  This ability makes bootstrap very popular.

The Bootstrap software can be obtained from:

https://getbootstrap.com/

The end user can click the "Download" button extract  the three files, and put them in every
directory page that uses bootstrap, or use a CDN (content delivery network), to use the files from a remote server, and
put those, on the top of every page that uses Bootstrap.  I will do both here, but comment out
the CDV, for learning purposes, but to keep the CDN and local files from conflicting.

The three folders, in the download, to include in all bootstrap pages:

css
fonts
js

The other method using the newest, Feb. 2020, version of bootstrap CDN:

CSS only:

<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.4.1/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-Vkoo8x4CGsO3+Hhxv8T/Q5PaXtkKtu6ug5TOeNV6gBiFeWPGFN9MuhOf23Q9Ifjh" crossorigin="anonymous">

JS, Popper.js, and jQuery:

<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.4.1.slim.min.js" integrity="sha384-J6qa4849blE2+poT4WnyKhv5vZF5SrPo0iEjwBvKU7imGFAV0wwj1yYfoRSJoZ+n" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/popper.js@1.16.0/dist/umd/popper.min.js" integrity="sha384-Q6E9RHvbIyZFJoft+2mJbHaEWldlvI9IOYy5n3zV9zzTtmI3UksdQRVvoxMfooAo" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
<script src="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.4.1/js/bootstrap.min.js" integrity="sha384-wfSDF2E50Y2D1uUdj0O3uMBJnjuUD4Ih7YwaYd1iqfktj0Uod8GCExl3Og8ifwB6" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>

The template, for index.html, contents, can be found here:

https://github.com/buckyroberts/Source-Code-from-Tutorials/blob/master/Bootstrap/001_template.html

We will now explain the CDNs line by line:

The viewport, in this first CDN, is essentially the viewer screen, the 'width' is the width of the screen and
'initial-scale'means do not zoom in or out in any special way; use regular zoom in every device:

<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">

The next on is where we get all the CSS default; styling, coloring and look of all the different widgets:

<link rel="stylesheet" href="http://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.4/css/bootstrap.min.css">

And the two script CDN's one is for the standard jquery library and the other for the javascript bootstrap file

<script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.11.3/jquery.min.js"></script>
<script src="http://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.4/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>

The <body> HERE </body>, will be the starting point for every boostrap page we make.

We will now start designing the website.  Almost everything within a website has to go in a container.  There are
two types of containers to choose from, for the 'class':

'container'      # a fixed size screen, container
'conainer-fluid' # full size scree, container

In the index.htm we will begin by setting up the container:

 <!--  set up the container size, heading a paragraph text-->
    <div class=" container">
        <h1>Welcome to Roddy's</h1>
        <p>We love theNewBoston, my name is Roddy</p>

    </div>

Then we will run this in PyCharm and view it on our browser.



